            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31419",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree, loading plugin resources on demand would be great enhancement.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-28T05:34:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-28T05:34:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33304",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blinky1ar",
                        "name": "blinky1ar",
                        "displayName": "blinky",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi check this post Initializing only one module per request in Zend_Framework at [easytech blog|http:\/\/blog.easytech.com.ar\/2009\/08\/04\/initializing-only-one-module-per-request-in-zend_framework\/]\nThis guys write some code to load only the resources for the module that is being called.\n \n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blinky1ar",
                        "name": "blinky1ar",
                        "displayName": "blinky",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-07T22:47:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-07T22:47:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33749",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If you have resources that need to be loaded only if a given module is selected, the appropriate place to do this is in a front controller plugin. \n\nZend_Application was designed to ease the burden of bootstrapping. One common issue encountered by developers was that they had configuration for modules that needed to be performed on each request: loading of module-specific routes (so that they can be matched against) and setting up autoloading for module resources. These activities could not be done easily prior to the introduction of Zend_Application.\n\nHowever, all along, if you've had resources that were module-specific and should only be run if the given module were selected, the appropriate time to load those was within a front controller plugin hook. As an example, if you don't need to initialize a DB for a given module unless that module will be used, do it during a preDispatch() hook in a Zend_Controller_Plugin -- and register the plugin as part of your module bootstrap.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-21T12:59:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-21T12:59:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33761",
                    "author": {
